Estonian

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

Perhaps from Swedish rädisa.

Noun

[edit]

redis (genitive redise, partitive redist)

  1. radish

Declension

[edit]

French

[edit]

Verb

[edit]

redis

  1. inflection of redire:
    1. first/second-person singular present/past historic indicative
    2. second-person singular imperative

Anagrams

[edit]
  • désir, rides

Latin

[edit]

Verb

[edit]

redīs

  1. second-person singular present active indicative of redeō

Portuguese

[edit]
